article.headline: Vermont 82, New Hampshire 79, 2OT
article.story: BURLINGTON, Vt. (AP) -- Chris Holm tallied 24 points and pulled down a career-high 18 rebounds while Mike Trimboli added 26 points as Vermont downed New Hampshire 82-79 in double overtime on Wednesday. The Catamounts' (16-6, 8-1 America East) Holm hit a lay-up to start the second overtime and Vermont would lead for the rest of the way. A Brandon Odom three-pointer with 1:46 left in the second overtime made it a one-point game, 80-79, but neither team would hit another bucket down the stretch. New Hampshire's (8-15, 4-6) Blagoj Janev had a chance to win it with three seconds left but his lay-up was blocked by Holm. Trimboli gathered the rebound and wrapped it up with a pair of free throws. Four Catamounts finished in double figures as Martin Klimes scored 12 and Kyle Cieplicki added 10. Janev scored a team-high 26 points for the Wildcats.
